# Example Environment Configuration

# This file shows example configurations for the AIditor API
# Copy this to .dev.vars for local development

# API Authentication Key
# Set this to a secure random string
API_KEY=your-secret-api-key-here

# Cloudflare D1 Database
# The database binding is configured in wrangler.toml
# For local development, wrangler will create a local SQLite database

# Example usage patterns:

## Material Pool Status Values
# - pending: Material collected but not yet processed
# - processing: Material currently being processed by AI
# - processed: Material successfully processed
# - failed: Material processing failed
# - archived: Material archived

## To-Publish Review Status Values
# - pending: Awaiting manual review
# - approved: Approved for publication
# - rejected: Rejected, not for publication
# - published: Successfully published to platform

## Supported Platforms (examples)
# - wechat: WeChat Official Account
# - weibo: Sina Weibo
# - toutiao: ByteDance Toutiao
# - zhihu: Zhihu
# - custom: Custom platform

# Note: These are just examples. You can define your own status values
# and platforms based on your requirements.
